		Makefile
		README




	Compile Instructions:
	
		Enter a2 directory and type "make". This creates exe named xsh




	Operating Instructions:
		
		Run shell by doing:
			
			./xsh
		
		Shell displays a prompt using class account username

		Valid formats for input:
			
			executablefilename
			executablefilename argument
			executablefilename | executablefilename
			executablefilename | executablefilename | ...
			exit


	Only non-piped commands may include one argument. Piped commands use 
	executable names only.

	To close --> type "exit"

	Design Decisions:

        - Functions are separated into multiple source files.

                main.cpp
                        - shell control
                        - executable validation
                        - command execution

                parser.cpp
                        - input parsing
                        - input validation
                        - command building

                pipeline.cpp
                        - pipeline execution

                shell.h
                        - shared function declarations

        - The USER environment variable is used to show the account username in the shell prompt.
        - When a command is entered without a slash, it is searched using the PATH environment variable.
        - Child processes are created using fork().
        - execvp() executes programs.
        - waitpid() waits for child processes to finish.
		

	No known bugs yet.

